132.2	Mesothelioma	Mesothelioma	Mesothelioma (or, more precisely, malignant mesothelioma) is a rare form of cancer that develops from transformed cells originating in the mesothelium, the protective lining that covers many of the internal organs of the body. It is usually caused by exposure to asbestos.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/MesotheliomaCT.jpg/235px-MesotheliomaCT.jpg
